1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,038
When working with JavaScript functions

2
00:00:02,413 --> 00:00:05,175
understanding the scope and context is crucial

3
00:00:06,150 --> 00:00:07,912
Functions create their own scope

4
00:00:08,137 --> 00:00:12,338
meaning variables declared within a function are not accessible outside of it

5
00:00:13,312 --> 00:00:13,850
Moreover

6
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:17,650
functions can access variables from the surrounding lexical scope

7
00:00:17,887 --> 00:00:18,938
known as closures

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:27,688
Knowing how to utilize closures effectively can greatly enhance your ability to write more flexible and efficient JavaScript code

